    "treatments": "Treatment of Torsades de Pointes typically involves addressing the underlying cause, such as correcting electrolyte imbalances or reviewing medications that may prolong the QT interval. Immediate interventions may include intravenous magnesium sulfate, which is effective in terminating TdP and stabilizing cardiac rhythm. In some cases, overdrive pacing may be employed to restore normal heart rhythm. For individuals with recurrent TdP, implantable cardioverter-defibrillators (ICDs) or medications like beta-blockers may be indicated as long-term management strategies."
